Telkom has announced that Jabu Mabuza has resigned as an independent non-executive director and chairman of the Telkom board. The resignation is effective 31 May 2019, and he will be replaced by Sello Moloko. Sello Moloko, an independent non-executive director on the Telkom board, is the non-executive chairman of Sibanye-Stillwater Limited and has chaired the board of Alexander Forbes, said Telkom. “Jabu Mabuza has chaired the Telkom board through some rough times since he joined in December 2012. On departure, he will leave a strong and stable organisation,” said Telkom CEO Sipho Maseko. Maseko said Mabuza’s leadership has been extremely valuable to Telkom.